================================================================
QUICK ESCALATION CHECKLIST
================================================================
 
1. sudo -l                          (sudo misconfig - most common)
2. find / -perm -4000 2>/dev/null   (SUID binaries)
3. getcap -r / 2>/dev/null          (capabilities)
4. cat /etc/crontab                 (cron jobs)
5. find / -writable -type f         (writable files)
6. ls -la /etc/passwd /etc/shadow   (writable critical files)
7. env / bash_history               (credentials in environment)
8. uname -a / cat /etc/os-release   (kernel exploits)
9. Run LinPEAS for full automation
 
